explanation: To analyze if parse_cookie_header contains dead code, the behavior and effects of its function calls must be understood. MHD_lookup_connection_value_n is required because it retrieves the cookie header; if it never returns MHD_NO or always returns empty, parts of the code would be dead. MHD_connection_alloc_memory_ is required to determine if memory allocation can fail; if it never fails, the failure branch might be dead. parse_cookies_string is critical because it produces parse_res, which controls the switch statement and affects subsequent control flow; understanding its behavior is essential to see if any switch cases are unreachable. MHD_DLOG is included as it is called in various switch cases; if these calls have no side effects or are never executed, the related code might be dead. Therefore, all these symbols influence control flow or side effects important for establishing the presence of dead code in parse_cookie_header.
